narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's required for midshipman, so for NROTC you have to take this course. But for non-NROTC students interested in the basic structure of the Navy, the military, and navy life, take this course! It isn't a ton of work and you will learn a lot.

If you are interested in learning about the structure of the Navy, its mission, and how it functions, I would recommend this. Just keep in mind that it does not count toward graduation credit and is filled with only NROTC students.
Basic introduction to the Navy and all its functions. Unless it receives credit in the future, there is no reason to take the course unless you are in NROTC.
The class is a necessary requirement for NROTC midshipmen, therefore I feel inclined to recommend the class.
